# Testing and Quality Rules
- Before phase completion, run lint, typecheck, build, and relevant tests.
- Add unit tests for pure rules, integration tests for persistence boundaries, and E2E tests for critical flows.
- Prioritize E2E coverage for auth, payment callbacks, stock reservation/finalization, order lifecycle, loyalty, and authorization.
- Test transaction rollback and concurrency-sensitive paths explicitly.
- Never ignore failing tests, suppress type errors casually, or merge unverifiable changes.
